<para> The Single-Tier ODBC Drivers for DB2 conform to the common architectural perceptions of an ODBC driver -- a single component installed on a desktop, workstation, or application server machine that depends on additional database specific networking middleware (from the relevant database vendor) for local or remote database connectivity.</para><para>The <ulink url="OpenLink">OpenLink</ulink>  Single-Tier Drivers for DB2 are a Type A class driver developed using the DB2CLI call level interface and assumes the prior installation of DB2Connect depending on your DB2 Server release.</para><para>These drivers are currently available for DB2 versions 6.x, 7.x, 8.x and beyond.</para><para>  [[/images/aodbcst.gif|]]</para><para> /DB2 Single-Tier Architecture Diagram Image scaled down; Click to enlarge./</para><para> This driver is available for Windows Operating systems.</para><para> </para></section></docbook>